{"TopicId":117809,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"kerbal scarecrow glitch","CreatedByName":"carneyvich","CreatedById":147880,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-06T18:57:37Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"carneyvich","CreatedById":147880,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-06T18:57:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ESo i was \u0022experimenting\u0022 with rockets and this happened..\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022%5Bimg%5Dhttp%3A//i.imgur.com/5m7jxv3.png\u0022 alt=\u00225m7jxv3.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GDJ","CreatedById":58462,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-06T19:01:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EKinda jumps in a single spot and holds it\u0027s arms out, like a dancer?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mitchz95","CreatedById":82292,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-06T19:10:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EGo into your persistence file and find him. Make sure he\u0027s listed as EVA and not Debris, Station, etc.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tanner Rawlings","CreatedById":58414,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-06T19:55:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Ewhen this happens i just say \u0022well, she/he just got shell shock, time for them to retire...\u0022\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"match","CreatedById":91708,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-06T20:30:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EGet another Kerbal to walk up and ask, \u0022Can I have your science?\u0022\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Overland","CreatedById":119812,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-07T03:51:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Eyou must have clicked on him with the \u0022blocker\u0022 icon instead of the climber or umbrella..\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Esadly as you cant send a basher to dig under him youll have to just double click the nuke once all the lemmings..err kerbals go home \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"User Unrelated","CreatedById":74021,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-07T11:13:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Overland\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Overland\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003Eyou must have clicked on him with the \u0022blocker\u0022 icon instead of the climber or umbrella..\u003Cp\u003Esadly as you cant send a basher to dig under him youll have to just double click the nuke once all the lemmings..err kerbals go home \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe only problem here is that Kerbals are free to move about the 3rd dimension.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI still have/play Lemmings for Gameboy Color \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Reactordrone","CreatedById":110060,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-07T11:20:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027ve had that happen a few times while I\u0027ve had multiple Kerbals on EVA. They can move around and hold onto ladders and climb, it\u0027s just that the movement animations don\u0027t work so not a huge issue.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EETA- it makes for some powerful BO when they\u0027re on EVA. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v499/swampmonster/screenshot1295_zpskmtyhfr4.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022screenshot1295_zpskmtyhfr4.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\